results.name: Wmns Fresh Foam Cruzv1 Reissue Wide 'White Cloud Pink'
results.story: The New Balance women’s Fresh Foam Cruzv1 Reissue Wide ‘White Cloud Pink’ highlights pastel hues on a lightweight, minimalist runner that provides sock-like comfort and a smooth ride. The breathable textile knit upper is secured with laces that are integrated into a supportive midfoot saddle, constructed from synthetic leather and decorated with signature ‘N’ branding. A cushy Fresh Foam midsole is reinforced underfoot by a grippy gum rubber outsole.

results.name: Numeric 1010 'Black'
results.story: Designed for pro skater Tiago Lemos, the New Balance Numeric 1010 ‘Black’ blends a throwback ‘90s aesthetic with modern performance benefits. The upper is crafted from breathable mesh with no-sew skins and black suede overlays throughout. An Ortholite sockliner combines with a FuelCell foam midsole for lightweight, responsive cushioning. Underfoot, a blue-tinged semi-translucent rubber outsole offers enhanced traction and board feel.

results.name: ACG Air Deschutz 'Dark Teal'
results.story: The Nike ACG Air Deschutz ‘Dark Teal’ applies contrasting hits of color to the outdoor sandal’s adjustable straps. Lightly padded and made with quick-drying materials, the straps deliver a custom fit by securing the forefoot, ankle and heel. Lightweight cushioning comes courtesy of a full-length foam midsole with an encapsulated Nike Air unit nestled in the heel. Underfoot, a grippy rubber outsole provides reliable traction on or off the trail.

results.name: Wmns Fresh Foam Cruzv1 Reissue 'White Cloud Pink'
results.story: The New Balance women’s Fresh Foam Cruzv1 Reissue ‘White Cloud Pink’ delivers a sock-like running shoe that pairs an airy build with a pastel color palette. A webbing pull tab at the heel allows easy entry into an engineered knit upper, reinforced with a molded Foam Comfort Heel and a synthetic leather midfoot cage stamped with New Balance’s ‘N’ logo. The slip-on construction is mounted on a Fresh Foam midsole that yields plush cushioning with each step.

results.name: Y-3 Runner 4D IOW 'Black'
results.story: The adidas Y-3 Runner 4D IOW ‘Black’ showcases a sleek finish on a versatile runner that comes with detachable details. Wearers can opt for a Primeknit sock or a more conventional sockliner and removable tongue. A black mesh overlay envelops the upper and extends to the groundbreaking 3D-printed midsole, crafted from a blend of light, oxygen and liquid resin. Lattice-like sidewalls are exposed through cutaway detailing around the forefoot.

Roma Basic Plus 'White Star Sapphire'
results.story: The PUMA Roma Basic Plus ‘White Star Sapphire’ delivers a refreshed iteration of the retro silhouette drawn from the brand’s late ‘60s archive. The low-top makes use of a crisp white leather upper with a tonal T-toe overlay and contrasting blue Formstrip. Metallic gold branding shines on the heel tab and lateral quarter panel. Lightweight cushioning is provided by a compression-molded EVA midsole, reinforced by a rubber outsole with an exaggerated herringbone tread for reliable grip.

Wmns UltraBoost 4.0 DNA 'White Cream'
results.story: The adidas women’s UltraBoost 4.0 DNA ‘White Cream’ utilizes a Primeknit upper in a subtle blend of tan and cream fibers. The breathable knit build, made in part with Parley Ocean Plastic and lined in comfortable textile, rests on a full-length Boost midsole in a pristine white finish. Branding hits include a discreet adidas tongue tag and ‘UltraBoost’ embossed on the molded heel counter. Underfoot, a Stretchweb Continental rubber outsole delivers optimal grip.

results.name: UltraBoost DNA CC_1 'Cloud White Gradient'
results.story: The adidas UltraBoost DNA CC_1 ‘Cloud White Gradient’ takes inspiration from the cult-favorite ClimaCool 1, highlighted by a textured Primeknit upper that incorporates Parley Ocean Plastic. Further nods to the retro silhouette include a two-tone ClimaCool tongue tag and a layered RPU cage with ventilated air channels. Responsive cushioning arrives via a full-length Boost midsole, rendered in a gradient blue finish and supported by a Stretchweb Continental rubber outsole.

UltraBoost 4.0 DNA 'Grey'
results.story: The adidas UltraBoost 4.0 DNA ‘Grey’ dresses the lightweight running shoe in a charcoal Primeknit upper made in part with Parley Ocean Plastic. The sneaker’s lacing system is integrated into the midfoot cage for a lockdown fit, while a molded heel counter cradles the back of the foot for enhanced support and stability. Energy return is generated by a full-length Boost midsole, which is supported underfoot by a flexible Stretchweb outsole built with grippy Continental rubber.

Roma Basic Plus 'Star Sapphire'
results.story: The PUMA Roma Basic Plus ‘Star Sapphire’ applies a simple two-tone finish to the vintage trainer originally released in 1968. The blue leather upper is reinforced with a signature T-toe overlay and accented with an off-white PUMA Formstrip. A gold-foil PUMA Roma callout is stamped on the lateral side, while the brand’s archive label adorns the padded tongue. The low-top rests on a compression-molded EVA midsole that offers lightweight cushioning with each step.

Air Zoom Victory Tour 2 Wide 'Black Metallic Pewter'
results.story: The Nike Air Zoom Victory Tour 2 Wide ‘Black Metallic Pewter’ pairs responsive cushioning with a premium build. The performance golf shoe makes use of a streamlined upper constructed from full-grain leather in a stealthy black finish. A padded, low-cut collar provides a comfortable fit, while an internal strap offers a feeling of lockdown. A Zoom Air unit stitched directly onto the upper works in tandem with a full-length plate to deliver energy return with each step. Underfoot, the hybrid outsole combines an integrated traction pattern with seven removable spikes for maximum grip.

results.name: adidas Forum Low Bad Bunny Pink Easter Egg
results.story: The Bad Bunny x adidas Forum Buckle Low ‘Easter Egg’ represents the pastel-colored follow-up to the duo’s inaugural ‘First Cafe’ collaboration, which preceded this holiday-themed release by less than a month. adidas’ retro hoops shoe is updated with a leather and suede build, rendered in subtle pink and coral hues and revamped with modern details. They include an adjustable ankle strap and doubled-up tongues, both featuring Bad Bunny’s third-eye logo. A durable rubber cupsole with semi-translucent sidewalls anchors the low-top.
